  "prompt": "How do you reduce the magnification of your screen?",
  "response": "The method to reduce screen magnification depends on your operating system:\n\nWindows:\n1. Hold down the Ctrl key and scroll down with mouse wheel\n2. Or use Windows key + minus (-)\n3. In Ease of Access, you can adjust Magnifier settings\n\nMac:\n1. Hold down Ctrl and pinch two fingers together on trackpad\n2. Or go to System Preferences > Accessibility > Zoom\n3. Use keyboard shortcut Option + Command + = (minus)\n\nChromebook:\n1. Ctrl + Minus (-)\n2. Use two-finger pinch gesture on touchpad\n\nMobile Devices:\n1. Pinch outward with two fingers on touchscreen\n2. In accessibility settings, you can adjust zoom levels\n\nEach device might have slightly different specific steps, but these are general methods for reducing screen magnification.",
